    "Thus, by our choice of ε, η and K,3 4 ≤ 1 4 + 1 4, a contradiction.Let us now recall Definition 3.7.",
    "The space P d is an appropriately quotiented space of formal Lipschitz sums and the map Em: P d → L ∞ is given by Em([i (f i, π i)]) = i f i det Dπ i ∈ L ∞.In the language of functional analysis, Theorem 5.23 tells us that for any σ ∈ 2B L ∞ and a weak * open neighbourhood V of σ, we find ρ 0 ∈ V ∩ 2B L ∞ together with a weak * open neighbourhood U such that U ∩ Em(SB P d) = ∅.",
    "This immediately implies that2B L ∞ \\ Em(SB P d) ⊃ U = σ,V U σ,V,where the union is taken over all σ ∈ 2B L ∞ and weak * open neighbourhoods V of σ and U σ,V is any open set having the property described for U above.",
    "In particular, the set U is weak * dense and open.",
    "It follows by taking complements, that 2B L ∞ ∩ Em(SB P d) can be covered by a weak * nowhere dense set (meaning intuitively that it is very small)."
